parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden acceleration or loss of throttle control can cause accidents, injuries, and damage to property. It can also lead to a loss of vehicle control, which can be particularly dangerous at high speeds.
symptoms: the engine speed drops to idle
the vehicle hesitates or lags when accelerating
the vehicle's speed control linkages fail.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the TPS can cause the vehicle to lose throttle control, leading to sudden acceleration or hesitation, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The engine speed drops to idle
the vehicle hesitates or lags when accelerating
the TPS becomes wet and fails to function.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the VSC system can cause the vehicle to lose traction and control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The VSC system fails to activate

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning dashboard electronics can cause intermittent or complete loss of critical instrument cluster functions, such as the odometer and speedometer, which can compromise the driver's ability to operate the vehicle safely.
symptoms: The odometer and speedometer work intermittently or not at all
the dashboard panel fails to function

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hood lift cylinders can cause the hood to suddenly fall, creating a safety hazard for individuals working under the hood, potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The hood falls unexpectedly while working under the hood
the hood does not stay open
the hood lift cylinders are unable to hold the weight of the hood.
